# 📖 Dream Weaver — Full Project Analysis

## 1. What Is This Project?

**Dream Weaver** (named *Interactive Bedtime Stories* in the README) is an AI-powered personalized bedtime story app for children. A parent enters a story idea and their child's details; the app generates a full illustrated, narrated, branching story — scene by scene — driven by the child's choices.

---

## 2. Tech Stack at a Glance

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|-----------|
| **Frontend** | React 19 + TypeScript (TSX), bundled with Vite 6 |
| **Backend** | Python 3.12 + FastAPI (async) |
| **AI Text** | OpenRouter → GPT-4o |
| **AI Audio (TTS)** | OpenRouter → gpt-4o-audio-preview (PCM16 @ 24kHz) |
| **AI Image** | OpenRouter → GPT-4o (base64 PNG) |
| **Pipeline Orchestration** | LangGraph (node-based async pipeline) |
| **Session Storage** | In-memory Python dicts (no database) |
| **Build Tool** | Vite 6 + `@vitejs/plugin-react` |
| **3rd Party UI** | `page-flip` (realistic book page turn animation) |

---

## 3. Architecture — How It All Works

### 3.1 Fire-and-Poll Model

```
Frontend (React)          Backend (FastAPI)
    │                           │
    │──POST /story/generate ───►│  Creates job, fires background task
    │◄── { session_id, job_id }─│  Returns immediately
    │                           │
    │──GET /story/status/{id} ──►   Polls every 2s
    │◄── { status: "complete" }─│
    │                           │
    │──GET /story/result/{id} ──►
    │◄── Scene payload ─────────│
```

All AI generation is **asynchronous**. The frontend never blocks — it submits and polls. This keeps the UI totally responsive.

### 3.2 Pre-generation Strategy (Key innovation)

After displaying any scene, the frontend **immediately fires one background generation job per choice** before the child picks one. This means when the child taps a choice, the next scene is already ready — **instant transition**. If it's not yet done, it falls back to a polling wait.

```
Scene displayed (step N)
    ├── prefireNextChapterJobs()
    │       ├── POST /story/generate → job A (for Choice 1)
    │       └── POST /story/generate → job B (for Choice 2)
Child picks Choice 1
    └── job A result cached? → instant swap → scene N+1 shown
```

### 3.3 Backend Pipeline (per scene)

```
node_generate_text
    └── LLM generates story prose + 2 choices
    └── parse_response() extracts [Choice A: ...] / [Choice B: ...]

node_generate_media  (runs concurrently)
    ├── TTS → audio WAV (base64)
    └── Image → illustration PNG (base64)

node_assemble
    └── Packages everything into SceneOutput
```

---

## 4. Frontend — Every File Explained

### 4.1 [index.tsx](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/index.tsx) — App Entry Point
The minimal React entry file. Finds `#root` in the DOM and mounts the `<App />` component using React 19's `createRoot`.

---

### 4.2 [index.html](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/index.html) — HTML Shell
The Vite-managed HTML entry point. Loads Google Fonts (Cinzel, Crimson Text), defines base CSS variables, animation keyframes (`fadeIn`, `hero-book-entry`, `book-glow-pulse`, `spin-ring`, wave bars), and references the React app via `<script type="module" src="/index.tsx">`.

---

### 4.3 [types.ts](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/types.ts) — Shared TypeScript Types

Defines the entire frontend data contract:

| Type | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| [Choice](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/types.ts#2-6) | `{ id, text }` — a story branch option |
| [Scene](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/types.ts#7-16) | Full scene payload: text, base64 audio, base64 image, choices, step number, session ID, `is_ending` flag |
| [PrefiredJob](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/types.ts#18-22) | Tracks a pre-generated branch: `{ choiceText, jobId }` |
| [StoryState](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/types.ts#23-29) | App-level state: `sessionId`, `currentScene`, [status](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/backend/main.py#344-350) (6 possible states), `error` |
| [StoryConfig](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/types.ts#30-44) | Personalization form data: child name, age, food, color, activity, pet, friends, family, photo |
| `DEFAULT_CONFIG` | Empty [StoryConfig](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/types.ts#30-44) used as the initial form state |

---

### 4.4 [App.tsx](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/App.tsx) — Main Application Shell

The brain of the frontend. Manages the **entire app state machine**:

#### State machine (6 statuses)
| Status | Meaning |
|--------|---------|
| `idle` | Landing page, prompt input shown |
| `starting` | Request sent to backend, waiting for job_id |
| `polling` | Actively polling `/story/status/:id` every 2s |
| `scene_ready` | First scene received, showing intro video |
| `ready` | Scene visible in the Book component |
| `error` | Something went wrong |

#### Key responsibilities
- **[handleStart](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/App.tsx#231-250)** — collects child config + story idea, POSTs to `/story/generate`, begins polling
- **`startPolling`** — runs a `setInterval` every 2s to check job status
- **`prefireNextChapterJobs`** — fires one generate request per choice, immediately after scene display
- **`handleContinue`** — transitions from IntroScreen → Book, plays first audio
- **`handleChoice`** — checks if the chosen branch is cached (instant swap) or falls back to polling
- **Background loop** — a separate `setInterval` runs every 2s to silently cache any ready pre-fired jobs

#### UI layers rendered (all stacked as `position: fixed`)
1. Parchment gradient background
2. SVG paper texture noise overlay
3. `<LandingCanvas />` — animated golden particles
4. Prompt input + closed book image (idle state)
5. `<IntroScreen />` — intro video while story generates
6. `<Book />` — the main reading interface
7. `<ConfigurationPage />` — personalization modal
8. Error screen ("A Great Calamity")

#### IntroScreen (inline component in App.tsx)
Shows the `/BedtimeStoryIntro.mp4` video while the story generates. Has Play/Pause/Restart controls and a status indicator (spinning ring → green dot when story is ready). The "Open the Book" button is disabled until `scene_ready`.

---

### 4.5 [components/Book.tsx](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/components/Book.tsx) — The Story Reader

The most complex component. Renders a realistic two-page open book with:

#### Left page — Illustration
- Displays `scene.illustration_b64` as a full-bleed image
- Shows chapter number in Cinzel font below the image

#### Right page — Story text + choices
- Scrollable story text in italic Crimson Text serif
- Chapter heading ("The Journey Begins" / "The Story Continues…")
- Choice buttons (disabled while `isGenerating`, shows a spinner when next scene is being fetched)
- "The End" shown instead of choices when `scene.is_ending === true`

#### Page flip animation (`page-flip` library)
- Uses `PageFlip` to create a realistic book page-turn animation
- When a new scene arrives, two new DOM pages are appended and `flipNext()` is triggered with an 80ms delay
- Automatically re-initializes when the container resizes (`ResizeObserver`)

#### Audio system
- Accepts an `audioRef` from [App.tsx](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/App.tsx) (so App can pre-start audio before Book mounts)
- Uses a `data-scene-id` attribute on the `<audio>` element as a tag — if App already started playing, Book skips reloading
- Falls back to creating a Blob URL from base64 audio if App hasn't loaded it yet
- Shows animated wave bars and play/pause button
- Shows "▶ tap to hear" hint if browser blocked autoplay

---

### 4.6 [components/ConfigurationPage.tsx](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/components/ConfigurationPage.tsx) — Personalization Modal

A full-screen modal overlay (blur backdrop) with a parchment-styled form:

| Section | Fields |
|---------|--------|
| **Child Profile** | Name (text), Age (range slider 1–8) |
| **Favorites** | Food, Color, Activity (each with preset dropdown + "Custom..." option) |
| **Companions & Family** | Pet name + type, Best friend, Siblings, Parents, Grandparents |
| **Child Picture** | File upload (.jpg/.png) — converted to base64 data URL, previewed as a circular avatar |

All data is stored in [StoryConfig](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/types.ts#30-44) state in [App.tsx](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/App.tsx). On save, the config is passed to `storyService.startStory()` as the `childInfo`.

---

### 4.7 [components/LandingCanvas.tsx](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/components/LandingCanvas.tsx) — Particle Animation

A `<canvas>` element rendered over the landing page background. It:
- Creates up to **7 tiny golden dust particles** (`MAX_PARTICLES = 7`)
- Each particle floats upward slowly (~20 seconds to cross the screen) with gentle horizontal drift
- Rendered using `requestAnimationFrame` for smooth 60fps animation
- Opacity oscillates using a sine wave (max ~4% opacity — extremely subtle)
- **Respects `prefers-reduced-motion`** — skips on reduced-motion systems
- **Disabled on mobile** (`< 768px`) to save battery
- Can be paused/resumed via the `paused` prop (controlled by the pause button in [App.tsx](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/App.tsx))

---

### 4.8 [services/storyService.ts](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/services/storyService.ts) — API Service Layer

Centralized module for all backend communication. Connects to `http://localhost:8000`.

| Method | Endpoint | Purpose |
|--------|----------|---------|
| [startStory()](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/services/storyService.ts#10-34) | `POST /story/generate` | Begin a new story (first chapter) |
| [pregenerateNextChapter()](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/services/storyService.ts#35-63) | `POST /story/generate` | Pre-fire one branch for next chapter |
| [addCharacter()](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/services/storyService.ts#64-88) | `POST /story/character` | Add a side character reference image |
| [checkStatus()](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/services/storyService.ts#89-95) | `GET /story/status/:id` | Poll job status |
| [getResult()](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/services/storyService.ts#96-126) | `GET /story/result/:id` | Fetch completed scene |
| [checkAndCache()](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/services/storyService.ts#137-158) | Internal | Background: check status + download silently |
| [isResultCached()](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/services/storyService.ts#129-132) | Internal | Check if a job result is in memory |
| [getCompletedResult()](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/services/storyService.ts#133-136) | Internal | Return cached result (instant path) |
| [debugStt()](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/services/storyService.ts#160-185) | `POST /story/debug/stt` | Transcribe audio, compare to story text (diagnostic) |

**Result Cache** — an in-memory `Map<string, Scene>` stores downloaded scenes. Pre-fired job results are cached silently so that when the child picks a choice, the result is served instantly from memory.

