## 5. Backend — Every File Explained

### 5.1 [backend/main.py](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/backend/main.py) — FastAPI Application

The HTTP layer. All endpoints:

| Endpoint | Method | Purpose |
|----------|--------|---------|
| `/` | GET | Health check |
| `/story/generate` | POST | Unified: start story OR pregenerate next chapter |
| `/story/status/:id` | GET | Poll job status (accepts job_id or session_id) |
| `/story/result/:id` | GET | Fetch complete scene result |
| `/story/character` | POST | Add/update character reference image |
| `/story/start` | POST | Simple start (used in older frontend flow) |
| `/story/choose` | POST | Advance session + fire next generation |
| `/story/debug/stt` | POST | Whisper transcription diagnostic |
| `/generate/start` | POST | Legacy stub |
| `/generate/status/:id` | GET | Legacy status endpoint |

**Startup lifecycle** ([lifespan](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/backend/main.py#55-65)):
1. Checks [frontend/public/binaries.properties](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/public/binaries.properties) and downloads any missing assets (intro video, child photo) via [utils/download_assets.py](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/utils/download_assets.py)
2. Loads `child_photo_01.png` into memory as base64 — injected as protagonist reference image into every new session

**Mock mode** — `MOCK_PIPELINES=true` env var skips all real AI calls, returns synthetic scene data in 0.1s. Used for tests.

**Pre-generation history commit** — When firing next-round pre-gen jobs, the frontend sends `prev_job_id`. The backend then commits the selected branch's LLM assistant response into the live session history before snapshotting for new jobs. This keeps the conversation context accurate.

---

### 5.2 [backend/contracts.py](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/backend/contracts.py) — Pydantic Data Models

| Model | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| [ChildConfig](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/backend/contracts.py#21-26) | Name (max 30 chars), age (3–8), voice, personalization |
| [Personalization](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/backend/contracts.py#12-20) | Favourite colour, animal, food, activities, pet name/type, place |
| [CharacterRef](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/backend/contracts.py#28-42) | Named character with role (protagonist/side), base64 image, description |
| [GenerateRequest](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/backend/contracts.py#45-74) | Unified first/next chapter request body |
| [GenerateResponse](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/backend/contracts.py#75-78) | `{ session_id, job_id }` |
| [StoryStatus](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/backend/contracts.py#86-93) | Enum: `pending → generating_text → safety_check → generating_media → complete/failed` |
| [Choice](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/types.ts#2-6) | `{ id, text, audio_b64, image_b64 }` |
| [SceneOutput](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/backend/contracts.py#100-110) | Full scene: session_id, step_number, story_text, audio, illustration, choices, is_ending, timing |
| [JobState](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/backend/contracts.py#111-118) | Tracks one generation job: job_id, session_id, status, result, raw_text |
| [StoryState](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/frontend/types.ts#23-29) | Full session: messages (LLM history), config, story_idea, step_number, characters dict |

---

### 5.3 [backend/session_store.py](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/backend/session_store.py) — In-Memory Stores

Two dict-backed stores, all data lives **only in Python process memory** (no database):

- **`session_store`** — maps `session_id → StoryState` (grows with LLM conversation history per session)
- **`job_store`** — maps `job_id → JobState` (holds result + status for each generation job)

> ⚠️ All data is lost on server restart. No persistence is intentional — the app is stateless per-session.

---

### 5.4 [backend/orchestrator/pipeline.py](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/backend/orchestrator/pipeline.py) — LangGraph Pipeline

The core AI pipeline. A `LangGraph` graph with three nodes executed sequentially:

```
node_generate_text → node_generate_media → node_assemble
```

1. **`node_generate_text`** — sends the full conversation history + story config to GPT-4o, parses the response to extract prose + choices
2. **`node_generate_media`** — runs TTS (`tts.py`) and image generation (`image.py`) concurrently via `asyncio.gather`
3. **`node_assemble`** — packages everything into [SceneOutput](file:///Users/omraghu07/bedtime-stories-capstone/backend/contracts.py#100-110), optionally writes debug artefacts to `backend/debug_output/`

---

### 5.5 `backend/pipelines/` — AI Integration Modules

| File | What it does |
|------|-------------|
| `text.py` | Sends LLM messages to OpenRouter/GPT-4o, calls `parse_response()` to split narrative from `[Choice A/B:]` markers |
| `tts.py` | Calls `gpt-4o-audio-preview` via OpenRouter to generate WAV audio; returns base64-encoded PCM16 audio |
| `image.py` | Calls GPT-4o with a detailed image prompt; uses the session's character reference images for visual consistency; returns base64 PNG |
| `provider.py` | OpenRouter async client factory — manages API key injection and base URL (`https://openrouter.ai/api/v1`) |

---

### 5.6 `backend/config/prompts.yaml` — System Prompts

Contains the YAML-formatted system prompt given to the LLM at the start of each session. Defines the storytelling voice, format requirements (prose followed by `[Choice A:]` / `[Choice B:]`), child-appropriate constraints, and personalization injection points.

---

### 5.7 `backend/safety/filters.py` — Input Sanitization

Applied to all user-provided `ChildConfig` before it is stored or used. Strips or replaces potentially harmful/inappropriate content in child name, preferences, and story ideas before they reach the LLM prompt.

---

## 6. Data Flow — End to End

```
1. Parent fills ConfigurationPage → StoryConfig saved in React state
2. Parent types story idea → hits "Open the Book"
3. App.handleStart() → POST /story/generate (first chapter)
4. Backend creates session + job → returns { session_id, job_id }
5. App polls /story/status/:jobId every 2s
6. Backend runs pipeline: text → media → assemble
7. Job status → "complete"
8. App fetches /story/result/:jobId → Scene object
9. IntroScreen shows "Ready" → parent clicks "Open the Book"
10. Book.tsx renders: illustration (left), text + choices (right)
11. App.prefireNextChapterJobs() fires immediately for all choices
12. Each pre-fired job runs its own pipeline snapshot in parallel
13. Child picks a choice → App.handleChoice()
    └── If cached → instant scene swap + audio play
    └── If not ready → fallback polling
14. Repeat from step 10
```

---

## 7. App States & UI Transitions

```
idle
 │ (submit story idea)
 ▼
starting → polling
              │ (job complete)
              ▼
          scene_ready  ← shows IntroScreen (video playing)
              │ (parent clicks "Open the Book")
              ▼
           ready  ← shows Book component
              │ (child picks choice → cached)
              ▼ (instant)
           ready (new scene)
              │ (child picks choice → not cached)
              ▼ (polling again)
           polling → ready
```

---

## 8. Key Design Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|----------|-----------|
| **Fire-and-poll** instead of WebSocket | Simpler, stateless, works through any proxy/CDN |
| **Pre-generation per choice** | Eliminates perceived wait time — next scene ready before child decides |
| **In-memory session store** | Privacy-first: zero persistence, data never hits disk/cloud |
| **OpenRouter** as AI gateway | Single API key for text, audio, and image models |
| **Base64 for media** | Avoids needing a separate file server; audio/images embedded in JSON |
| **LangGraph pipeline** | Structured node-based async graph, easy to extend with new steps |
| **Protagonist reference image** | Server pre-loads `child_photo_01.png` so illustrations stay visually consistent |
| **`page-flip` library** | Provides authentic book page-turn physics with shadows |
| **Canvas particles** | Subtle magical ambiance; respects `prefers-reduced-motion` and skips on mobile |

---

## 9. Configuration & Environment

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` | Required — powers all AI calls |
| `OPENAI_API_KEY` | Optional — only for Whisper STT diagnostic endpoint |
| `DEBUG=true` | Writes every generated scene to `backend/debug_output/` as `.txt` / `.wav` / `.png` |
| `MOCK_PIPELINES=true` | Skips AI calls for fast local testing |

---

## 10. Testing Infrastructure

Located in `tests/test_pipeline_local.py`, layered by API key requirement:

| Level | Tests | Needs Key? |
|-------|-------|-----------|
| 1 — Unit | `parse_response`, pipeline logic, mocked AI calls | ❌ No |
| 2 — API | FastAPI endpoints via `TestClient` | ❌ No |
| 3 — Smoke | Single real calls to text/TTS/image | ✅ Yes |
| 4 — E2E | Full multi-turn story through live pipeline | ✅ Yes |

Level 3/4 tests auto-skip when `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` is not set.
